              "Description": "BG Chlor-Alkali Process - This prevention program is applied to the Cell Room, Liquefaction Area, SCR Ammonia system, and Marshalling Yard areas.  All prevention program elements are applied similarly to each area.  The Marshalling Yard is not a process unit but is a temporary storage area for railcars.  Consequently, PHA information is different for this area.  Among the PHA differences in Section 7.4 are:  A) Dates of the last PHAs for the Cell Room, Liquefaction, and SCR Ammonia system are 10/2006, 3/2007, and 7/2004, respectively.  B)   The PHA technique for this area is What If and Checklist, whereas the other PHAs additionally utilize HAZOP.  C) Expected or actual dates of completion of all changes from the Cell Room, Liquefaction, and Ammonia System PHA are 10/31/2007, 12/31/2010, and 6/30/2005.  D) Major hazards are the same for each area except that the Marshalling Yard does not have runaway reaction, overpressurization, overfilling, contamination, or loss of utility hazards.  E) The Marshalling Yard doesn't have process controls such as relief valves as they do not apply, whereas these are used in the other areas.  F) The other areas utilize mitigation systems, including dikes and neutralization systems.  The Ammonia system utilizes a deluge system.  G) Monitoring/detection systems include process area detectors that are in use for each area.  H) Changes made since the last PHAs include process parameters and process controls for all areas except the Ammonia System and Marshalling Yard.",
